				\begin{document}$$N > 0$$\end{document}N>0, one hundred percent of degree d hyperelliptic (resp. plane) curves C have at least N primes p of bad semistable reduction. The case \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
